## 2️⃣ HOME PAGE AS ORDERING ENGINE

### The Problem
Current [HomeView](file:///Users/nguyenducnhat/appcafe/thecoffeelinks-client-ios/thecoffeelinks-client-ios/HomeView.swift) shows:
1. Header greeting
2. QuickOrderWidget
3. Active order (if any)
4. Highlights carousel
5. "What's hot" (trending)
6. "Order again" (history)

**Issue:** Users still open Menu tab to browse. Home is not the ordering engine.

### The Vision: Home-as-Menu

> [!IMPORTANT]
> If the user opens Menu within 5 seconds of opening the app, Home has failed.

### Cognitive Load Analysis

| Items Visible | User State |
|---------------|------------|
| 1-3 | Decision-ready (optimal) |
| 4-6 | Slight scanning required |
| 7+ | Cognitive paralysis; user opens Menu |

**Recommendation:** Maximum 6 actionable items above the fold.

### Section Priority & Behavior

#### Above the Fold (Ordered by Priority)
1. **Ready-to-Order Card** (AI-generated, 1-tap checkout) ⬅️ NEW
2. **Your Usual** (existing [QuickOrderWidget](file:///Users/nguyenducnhat/appcafe/thecoffeelinks-client-ios/thecoffeelinks-client-ios/Views/QuickOrderWidget.swift))
3. **Active Order Banner** (if any)

#### Below the Fold (Scrollable)
4. **Favorites** (heart-marked items) ⬅️ NEW
5. **Popular Right Now** (location-based trending)
6. **Recommended for This Time** (context-aware)
7. **Highlights** (events/vouchers)

### Section Visibility Rules

| Section | Appears When | Disappears When |
|---------|--------------|-----------------|
| Ready-to-Order | User has 3+ past orders | User dismisses 3x consecutively |
| Your Usual | User has 1+ recorded order | Never (shows empty state) |
| Favorites | User has 1+ favorited item | No favorites |
| Popular Right Now | Store has real-time data | Store closed or <5 orders today |
| Recommended for Time | User has time-based pattern | No pattern detected |

### Adaptive Behavior

| Context | Home Adjustment |
|---------|-----------------|
| Morning (6-11am) | Lead with coffee; hide evening items |
| Rainy weather | Promote hot drinks, hide iced |
| Weekday 8-9am | "Your commute order" card |
| Weekend afternoon | Leisure vibes, show pastries |

