## 3️⃣ FAVORITES, NOTES & PERSONAL MEMORY

### Current Gap
No favorites system exists. [QuickOrderService](file:///Users/nguyenducnhat/appcafe/thecoffeelinks-client-ios/thecoffeelinks-client-ios/Services/QuickOrderService.swift) tracks frequency but not explicit preferences.

### Favorites Design

#### Where the Heart Icon Lives
- Product card (ProductCard, ProductRow) — tap to toggle
- Order confirmation — "Add to favorites?"
- Order history — each item has heart toggle

#### Favorites vs. History
| Aspect | Favorites | History/Your Usual |
|--------|-----------|-------------------|
| User intent | Explicit ("I love this") | Implicit (ordered frequently) |
| Customization | Saves exact config | Learns from repetition |
| Visibility | Always shown on Home | Shown based on scoring |

### Personal Notes System

#### UX Location
Notes attach to **Product-Customization pairs**, not raw products.

```
"Iced Latte (M, 50% sugar)"
📝 "For Monday meetings — less ice if afternoon"
```

#### Note Types
| Type | Example | Effect |
|------|---------|--------|
| Preference reminder | "Always ask for extra shot" | Shown at customization |
| Context cue | "Order this on Fridays" | Surfaces item on Fridays |
| Modification instruction | "No lid - drinking here" | Passed to store |

#### Speed Enhancement (Not Slowdown)
> [!TIP]
> Notes should ACCELERATE ordering, not add steps.

**Pattern:** Notes are **read-only during checkout**. Editing happens in Profile → Favorites.

```
Checkout item row:
  Iced Latte (M)
  📝 "Less ice, extra shot"  ← shown as info, not editable
```

### Avoiding Settings Nightmare
- Maximum 3 notes per item
- No nested note categories
- Notes are short-form (140 char max)
- "Smart notes" auto-extracted from repeated customizations

